Business Recommendations & Strategy

1. Target High-Risk Customers (Early Tenure)

Insight:
Customers with tenure < 24 months show significantly higher churn rates

Action:

Launch onboarding engagement programs
Offer early-stage discounts or bundled services

Business Impact:

Reduces early churn
Improves long-term customer retention
2. Reduce Churn in Month-to-Month Contracts

Insight:
Month-to-month customers have the highest churn (~40–45%)

Action:

Provide incentives (10–15% discount) for switching to annual plans
Introduce loyalty rewards for longer commitments

Business Impact:

Increases customer lifetime value
Stabilizes revenue streams
3. Improve Retention for Fiber Optic Customers

Insight:
Fiber optic users exhibit the highest churn rates (~45%)

Action:

Improve service quality and customer support
Offer personalized plans or pricing adjustments

Business Impact:

Retains high-value customers
Prevents revenue leakage
4. Focus on High-Value Customers (LTV-Based Retention)

Insight:
Retained customers generate ~50% higher lifetime value compared to churned customers

Action:

Identify high-LTV customers
Provide premium support and exclusive benefits

Business Impact:

Maximizes revenue
Improves ROI on retention efforts
5. Optimize Payment & Billing Experience

Insight:
Payment method and billing type influence churn behavior

Action:

Encourage automatic payments
Simplify billing experience

Business Impact:

Reduces friction
Improves customer satisfaction
